"{\"content\":{\"body\":\"In the research world, when we talk about the security and trustless properties of the encryption economy, we are actually asking a very specific question: who is verifying the systems and what is the cost of breaking them?\\n\\nIf our goal is to build a truly decentralized, uncensorable public product, we must consider: Our system may be attacked by very powerful opponents, such as sovereign states, large corporations, or arrogant evil geniuses .\\n\\nMaximizing security means maximizing the number and diversity of validators (validators, miners, etc.) in the system. This usually means doing your best to have a system that is fully verified by the Ethereum validator set—— This is the core idea behind the scalability of L2 and Ethereum.\",\"timestamp\":1634226745,\"title\":\"What does \\\"no trust\\\" mean in cryptoeconomics?\"},\"digest\":\"RdEgE0fY3-ZxvVHG93cHXkQtCXcDpEF2Br-ZD0axxZU\",\"authorship\":{\"contributor\":\"0x72d16a2d1a74CE69bdCB592A75bB99566c40798E\",\"signingKey\":\"{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"ZDjzD-2CwF9TU8H_CrWICjzE25UVIOmIBArfI6Iu3A8\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"E06vnh7hczFroIIAXiMt5wa3LPO6_wPdhhkfsJQkPR8\\\"}\",\"signature\":\"VmHmMy-eZZy0jxH1at5usWRs5Ne-qNoGlqhKSqmjCk1_vMZ2UEM_BgTZwrtb5hKxUdBWcq_01TthZgk7CBZLZw\",\"signingKeySignature\":\"0x1fc4cdde7eae4714a6d11ecedd748f0222dfd9c2097085cb36aa3851a3b818bd7ea083996566270d01ffc308fb71c015af1e7fd922395f5d9f5ac4e99233a7ec1b\",\"signingKeyMessage\":\"I authorize publishing on mirror.xyz from this device using:\\n{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"ZDjzD-2CwF9TU8H_CrWICjzE25UVIOmIBArfI6Iu3A8\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"E06vnh7hczFroIIAXiMt5wa3LPO6_wPdhhkfsJQkPR8\\\"}\",\"algorithm\":{\"name\":\"ECDSA\",\"hash\":\"SHA-256\"}},\"nft\":{},\"version\":\"12-21-2020\",\"originalDigest\":\"RdEgE0fY3-ZxvVHG93cHXkQtCXcDpEF2Br-ZD0axxZU\"}"